                        <additions>
                            <p>
                                <!--Identifiera MA och skriv in och tagga.-->
                                <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/>
                                <note>Top left corner: National Library book label with the current signum in black ink. Centre page: bookplate of Prince Borghese. Various notes in pencil by modern hands, from top to bottom: <quote>Borghesiska katalogen P. 2.1892</quote>; <quote>Antiphonarium s. 1-103</quote>; <quote>Hymnarium 104-119</quote>; <quote>L 2. (signavit Blume)</quote>; <quote xml:lang="sv">Photostatiskt reproducerad 30 maj-1 juni 1921 för fil. lic. Matts Åmark</quote>; in ink: <quote>Antiphonarium och Hymnarium sanctae Birgittae. Inköpt Febr. 1893 på Prins Borgheses bokauktion i Rom. - No. 938 i auktionskatalogen</quote>.</note>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <locus from="SL1v" to="SL1v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <note>Centre page: bookplate of Prince Borghese.</note>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <locus from="SR1r" to="SR1r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <note>Top right in pencil by modern hand: <quote>ma</quote>; bottom right in pencil by modern hand: <quote>z</quote>.</note>
                            </p>
                        </additions>
                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding contemporary="false">
                                <p>19th-century binding. Brown leather over medieval wooden boards. 4 double raised bands and 2 end-bands. 2 pin clasps attached to leather straps going from the <locus from="RCO" to="RCO" scheme="other"/>. <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/>, stamped in gold: <quote>A 84</quote>.</p>
                                <p>
                                    <dimensions type="binding">
                                        <height quantity="310" unit="mm"/>
                                        <width quantity="225" unit="mm"/>
                                        <depth quantity="40" unit="mm"/>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </p>
                                <decoNote type="tooling">
                                    <p>2-line blind tooling along the outer edges of the volume, creating a panel which is further divided by 2-line tooling in the form of an <quote>X</quote>.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                                <condition>Binding shows signs of wear. Cracking along the spine. The original brown leather straps still extant but have been reinforced with a new pair of tighter, white straps, in 1975. On <locus from="RCI" to="RCI" scheme="other"/>, signs of rust (?) from the nails attaching the straps.</condition>
                            </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>
                    </physDesc>
                    <history>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>Belonged to the Borghese family, see bookplate of <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102586">Marcantonio V Borghese</persName> on <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/>. Earlier provenance is unknown but <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107252">Geete (1895)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="lxxviii" to="lxxviii" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl> suggests the Birgittine monastery Paradiso near <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100021">Florence</placeName>, as does <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107180">Servatius (1990)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="53" to="53" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>, who also mentions Scala Coeli in <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100246">Genoa</placeName> or a house in <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100247">Valencia</placeName> as other possibilities.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition>
                            <p>Purchased by the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100004">National Library of Sweden</orgName> in <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100070">Rome</placeName>, in February <date when="1893"/> at the book auction of <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102571">Paolo Borghese</persName>, Prince of Sulmona, see addition on <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/>. The auction catalogue number mentioned there does not correspond to the number in the <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107293">Borghese auction catalogue</title>
                                </bibl>, where it is listed as no. 4564.</p>
                        </acquisition>
                    </history>
