                        <history>
                            <origin>
                                <p>
                                    Origin unknown, <origPlace>
                                        <placeName cert="low" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100081">Sweden</placeName>
                                        <placeName cert="low" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100101">Vadstena Abbey</placeName>
                                    </origPlace>. <origDate notAfter="1500" notBefore="1451">15th century, second half</origDate>. According to <bibl>
                                        <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107264">Nilsson (1992)</title>
                                        <citedRange from="28" to="28" unit="page"/>
                                    </bibl>, the hand is not Italian and the hymn melodies seem to conform to the Swedish tradition. <ref target="http://urn.kb.se/resolve?urn=urn:nbn:se:alvin:portal:record-472813">Lindqvist Sandgren</ref> claims that it was produced at Vadstena Abbey with the exception of the first and the last two folios which were made in <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100036">Italy</placeName>. <bibl>
                                        <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107180">Servatius (1990)</title>
                                        <citedRange from="53" to="54" unit="page"/>
                                    </bibl>, on the other hand, does not rule out an Italian origin for the whole manuscript.</p>
                            </origin>
                        </history>
